He storm shook the house violently, as he sat in a corner, wimpering. He was alone. maybe. Maybe not. A sound, faint but hearable. A creak, the man turned around. It was here. 
The man shivered as it came closer, slowly but surely. It reached out...
"No!" The man woke up startled, unsure of what it meant. It had to mean something. It had to. It always did. He stepped out of his room, 
